# Audio Beats in Linux

## Tested in my laptop hp envy 15-j013cl with Elementary Loki

![Envy laptop][envy-lap] ![elementary][elementary-logo]

>It is good to have the music back :) :tada:

### To get the Audio Beats work in linux

1. Run the command: *`sudo apt update && sudo apt install alsa-tools-gui`*.
1. Now see left corner `Applications` -> `Sound and Video` and click in **HDAJackRetask.**
1. In the first dropbox `Select a codec:` select the **`92HD91BXX`**.
1. in he right menu `Options`, select the checkbox `Show unconnected pins`.
1. In the Pin ID: **`0x0d`**, check `Override` and select `Internal speaker`. Do the same with the pin **`0x0f`**.
1. With the pin **`0x10`**, select `Internal speaker (LFE`)
1. Do some test of sound with music or the test sound option.
1. Hit the `Apply now` in the down right corner.
1. In the mode section, the `Analog Stereo Output` gives me louder sound.
   - But, IMO with the `Analog surround 4.0 Output` mode, the music sounds better.
1. If all is good, click in the *`Install boot override`*.
1. Reboot and check if all still working.
1. **Enjoy!**
